25
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:33,780
I can read about it.

26
00:01:33,780 --> 00:01:37,780
Still why should I say I don't know anything about Derbyshire?

27
00:01:37,780 --> 00:01:40,140
Because I have not been to Derbyshire before.

28
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:45,100
I have not been to Derby, I have not been to this area, I have not seen this place, I have

29
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,100
not visited it.

30
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:50,780
I have had no experience of this place, so I don't know about it.

31
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:53,620
This is exactly what is the situation.

32
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:59,500
The situation is that we do not know about the Divine, we have read about it, we have heard

33
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,020
about it.

34
00:02:01,020 --> 00:02:05,540
So many people have written about it, once they know there's an inquiry about it, they

35
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:10,340
come out with books, books after books, thousands of books have written.

36
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:13,660
How many of them are true and how many of them are untrue?

37
00:02:13,660 --> 00:02:16,060
It is impossible to find out.

38
00:02:16,060 --> 00:02:19,580
Because we do not actually know.

39
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:26,300
Supposing somebody says that Duke of Bedford was born in Derbyshire, all right, how will

40
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,300
I know?

